Step-by-StepPrp5:CreateJenkinsPipelineJob 1.OpenJenkinsDashboard→NewItem→SelectPipeline. 2.InPipelinesettings→choosePipelinescriptfromSCM. 3.SelectGit→ProvideGitHubrepositoryURL. 4.JenkinswillautomaticallydetectJenkinsfileandexecutestages. Step6:RunandMonitorthePipeline 1.SavethePipelinejobafterenteringtheGitHubrepositoryURL. 2.OnthePipelinedashboard,clickBuildNowtotriggerthepipelinemanually forthefirsttime. 3.Jenkinswillnow: oCloneyourGitHubrepository. oDetecttheJenkinsfile. oExecutestagesdefinedinside(BuildDockerImage→RunContainer). 4.Clickonthebuildnumber(e.g.,#1)→ConsoleOutputtomonitorthepipelinelogsinrealtime. Step7:VerifytheApplication 1.Oncethebuildissuccessful,openabrowserandvisit: http://localhost:5000 2.YoushouldseeyourUserRegistrationApprunninginsidetheDockercontainerlaunchedbyJenkins. Step8:SetUpAutomaticBuilds(OptionalbutRecommended) TomaketheCI/CDworkflowseamless: 1.GotoyourPipelinejob→Configure. 2.UnderBuildTriggers,enable: oPollSCM(JenkinschecksGitHubrepoatintervals). 3.ThisensuresthatwheneveryoupushnewcodetoGitHub,Jenkinswillautomaticallybuildanddeploy theupdatedDockercontainer.ocedure: Step1:VerifyDockerisWorking docker--version dockerinfo Step2:BuildandRunLocally •OpenPowerShell/CMD. •Moveintoyourprojectdirectory •BuildtheDockerimage: dockerbuild-tweek-2. (.means“usethecurrentdirectory”asbuildcontext,soyoumustbeinsidethe appfolder) •Runthecontainer: dockerrun-p5000:5000week-2 •Openabrowserandvisit: http://localhost:5000 ForIntegratingJenkinsandDockerdothestepsbelow [Whateverfilesyouprepareinyourlocalrepository(e.g.,app.py,Dockerfile,requirements.txt,Jenkinsfile, HTMLtemplates,etc.)shouldbesavedexactlythesamewayinyourGitHubrepository.] Step3:PushCodetoGitHub CommitDockerfile,requirements.txt,andJenkinsfileintoyourrepository. Step4:ConfigureJenkinswithDocker 1.OpenJenkins→ManageJenkins→Plugins. 2.InstallDockerplugin. 3.ConfigureDockerInstallationinJenkins ➢GotoManageJenkins→Tools ➢ScrolltoDockersection. ➢ClickAddDocker→giveitaname(e.g.,docker). ➢Leave“Installautomatically”unchecked(sinceDockerDesktopisalreadyinstalledonWindows). ➢addGitinstallation,andgiveitanamelikeDefaultGit. 5.Savetheconfiguration. Name:Shravani RollN
